#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn1.35"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn1.35:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 1 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 1 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.35:0.2"
msgid "4. Satullapakāyikavagga "
msgstr "4. The Satullapa Group "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn1.35:0.3"
msgid "35. Ujjhānasaññisutta "
msgstr "35. Disdain "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.24, sc1
msgctxt "sn1.35:1.1"
msgid "Ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā sāvatthiyaṃ viharati jetavane anāthapiṇḍikassa ārāme. "
msgstr "At one time the Buddha was staying near Sāvatthī in Jeta’s Grove, Anāthapiṇḍika’s monastery. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.35:1.2"
msgid "Atha kho sambahulā ujjhānasaññikā devatāyo abhikkantāya rattiyā abhikkantavaṇṇā kevalakappaṃ jetavanaṃ obhāsetvā yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkamiṃsu; upasaṅkamitvā vehāsaṃ aṭṭhaṃsu. "
msgstr "Then, late at night, several glorious deities of the Disdainful Group, lighting up the entire Jeta’s Grove, went up to the Buddha, and stood in the air. "

msgctxt "sn1.35:1.3"
msgid "Vehāsaṃ ṭhitā kho ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "Standing in the air, one deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.1"
msgid "“Aññathā santamattānaṃ, "
msgstr "“Someone who pretends "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.2"
msgid "aññathā yo pavedaye; "
msgstr "to be other than they really are, "

# NOTE: See BB for kitava
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.3"
msgid "Nikacca kitavasseva, "
msgstr "is like a cheating gambler "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:2.4"
msgid "bhuttaṃ theyyena tassa taṃ. "
msgstr "who enjoys what was gained by theft. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.50, sc3
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.1"
msgid "Yañhi kayirā tañhi vade, "
msgstr "You should only say what you would do; "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.2"
msgid "yaṃ na kayirā na taṃ vade; "
msgstr "you shouldn’t say what you wouldn’t do. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.3"
msgid "Akarontaṃ bhāsamānaṃ, "
msgstr "The wise will recognize "

# NOTE: BB has two separate devas speaking here, presumably following the comm. But the text clearly indicates that it is a single deva, and the close -ti is only found here.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:3.4"
msgid "parijānanti paṇḍitā”ti. "
msgstr "one who talks without doing.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.1"
msgid "“Na yidaṃ bhāsitamattena, "
msgstr "“Not just by speaking, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.2"
msgid "ekantasavanena vā; "
msgstr "nor solely by listening, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.3"
msgid "Anukkamitave sakkā, "
msgstr "are you able to progress "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.4"
msgid "yāyaṃ paṭipadā daḷhā; "
msgstr "on this hard path, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.5"
msgid "Yāya dhīrā pamuccanti, "
msgstr "by which wise ones practicing absorption "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:4.6"
msgid "jhāyino mārabandhanā. "
msgstr "are released from Māra’s bonds. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.1"
msgid "Na ve dhīrā pakubbanti, "
msgstr "The wise certainly don’t act like that, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.2"
msgid "viditvā lokapariyāyaṃ; "
msgstr "for they understand the ways of the world. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.3"
msgid "Aññāya nibbutā dhīrā, "
msgstr "The wise are extinguished by understanding, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:5.4"
msgid "tiṇṇā loke visattikan”ti. "
msgstr "they’ve crossed over clinging to the world.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.51, sc6
msgctxt "sn1.35:6.1"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatāyo pathaviyaṃ patiṭṭhahitvā bhagavato pādesu sirasā nipatitvā bhagavantaṃ etadavocuṃ: "
msgstr "Then those deities landed on the ground, bowed with their heads at the Buddha’s feet and said, "

#. VAR: yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ → yathābālā yathāmūḷhā yathāakusalā (s1-3, km, pts1-2)
msgctxt "sn1.35:6.2"
msgid "“accayo no, bhante, accagamā yathābālaṃ yathāmūḷhaṃ yathāakusalaṃ, yā mayaṃ bhagavantaṃ āsādetabbaṃ amaññimhā. "
msgstr "“We have made a mistake, sir. It was foolish, stupid, and unskillful of us to imagine we could attack the Buddha! "

msgctxt "sn1.35:6.3"
msgid "Tāsaṃ no, bhante, bhagavā accayaṃ accayato paṭiggaṇhātu āyatiṃ saṃvarāyā”ti. "
msgstr "Please, sir, accept our mistake for what it is, so we will restrain ourselves in future.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.35:6.4"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā sitaṃ pātvākāsi. "
msgstr "At that, the Buddha smiled. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn1.35:6.5"
msgid "Atha kho tā devatāyo bhiyyoso mattāya ujjhāyantiyo vehāsaṃ abbhuggañchuṃ. "
msgstr "Then those deities, becoming even more disdainful, flew up in the air. "

msgctxt "sn1.35:6.6"
msgid "Ekā devatā bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi: "
msgstr "One deity recited this verse in the Buddha’s presence: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.1"
msgid "“Accayaṃ desayantīnaṃ, "
msgstr "“If you don’t give your pardon "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.2"
msgid "yo ce na paṭigaṇhati; "
msgstr "when a mistake is confessed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.3"
msgid "Kopantaro dosagaru, "
msgstr "with hidden anger and heavy hate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:7.4"
msgid "sa veraṃ paṭimuñcatī”ti. "
msgstr "you’re stuck in your enmity.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.52, sc8
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.1"
msgid "“Accayo ce na vijjetha, "
msgstr "“If no mistake is found, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: nocidhāpagataṃ → nocīdha apahataṃ (s1-3, km) | nocīdhāpagataṃ (pts1) | no cidhāpagataṃ (pts2) | nocidhāpakataṃ (?)
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.2"
msgid "nocidhāpagataṃ siyā; "
msgstr "if no-one’s gone astray, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.3"
msgid "Verāni na ca sammeyyuṃ, "
msgstr "and enmities are settled, "

# NOTE: the sense of this verse is a little obscure, see BB’s note. I suggest that an a-has been elided from kusala.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: kenīdha → tenīdha (bj) | ko nīdha (pts2)
msgctxt "sn1.35:8.4"
msgid "kenīdha kusalo siyā”ti. "
msgstr "then who could have been unskillful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc9
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.1"
msgid "“Kassaccayā na vijjanti, "
msgstr "“Who makes no mistakes? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.2"
msgid "kassa natthi apāgataṃ; "
msgstr "Who doesn’t go astray? "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.3"
msgid "Ko na sammohamāpādi, "
msgstr "Who doesn’t fall into confusion? "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: ca → ko cā (bj) | kodha (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn1.35:9.4"
msgid "ko ca dhīro sadā sato”ti. "
msgstr "Who is the wise one that’s ever mindful?” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts1ed1.25, sc10
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.1"
msgid "“Tathāgatassa buddhassa, "
msgstr "“The Realized One, the Buddha, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.2"
msgid "sabbabhūtānukampino; "
msgstr "compassionate for all beings: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.3"
msgid "Tassaccayā na vijjanti, "
msgstr "that’s who makes no mistakes, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.4"
msgid "tassa natthi apāgataṃ; "
msgstr "and that’s who doesn’t go astray. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.5"
msgid "So na sammohamāpādi, "
msgstr "He doesn’t fall into confusion, "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: sova → sodha (si, s1-3, km) | so ca (pts1)
msgctxt "sn1.35:10.6"
msgid "sova dhīro sadā satoti. "
msgstr "for he’s the wise one, ever mindful. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.53, sc11
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.1"
msgid "Accayaṃ desayantīnaṃ, "
msgstr "If you don’t give your pardon "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.2"
msgid "yo ce na paṭigaṇhati; "
msgstr "when a mistake is confessed, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.3"
msgid "Kopantaro dosagaru, "
msgstr "with hidden anger and heavy hate, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.4"
msgid "sa veraṃ paṭimuñcati; "
msgstr "you’re stuck in your enmity. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.5"
msgid "Taṃ veraṃ nābhinandāmi, "
msgstr "I don’t approve of such enmity, "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn1.35:11.6"
msgid "paṭiggaṇhāmi voccayan”ti. "
msgstr "and so I pardon your mistake.”"

#. HTML: </p></blockquote></article></section></body></html>
